license: OFL
category: serif
subsets: menu,latin

family: Fanwood Text

designer: Barry Schwartz

approved: true
description: <p>Based on Fairfield, the typeface first published \
  in 1940 and designed by Rudolph Ruzicka, a \
  famous Czech-American type designer. Fanwood Text roman and \
  italic are the same as Fanwood, but slightly darker and \
  reduced in contrast; this was tailored for increased \
  readability on the Amazon Kindle 3 e-book reader \
  hardware.</p> \
  <p>For more information about the typeface, read \
  the Wikipedia article on \
  <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fairfield_%28typeface%29">Fairfield</a>.</p> \
  <p>The fonts are available from the designer's own site, \
  <a href="http://sortsmill.googlecode.com">Sortmill</a>, with \
  a very liberal MIT-style license, and are made available here \
  and on the <a href="http://www.theleagueofmoveabletype.com/fonts/17-fanwood">League \
  of Movable Type</a> under the SIL OFL, without a Reserved Font \
  Name.</p>

font.FanwoodText-Regular.ttf.style: normal
font.FanwoodText-Italic.ttf.style: italic

font.FanwoodText-Regular.ttf.weight: 400
font.FanwoodText-Italic.ttf.weight: 400


